covered: GET Valid Request scenarios: default and no-parameter retrieval return 200 with an array of Account objects (TC01, TC43).
Empty Response handling: no accounts yields an empty array (TC08).
Pagination handling: offset/limit behavior and boundary tests (TC02, TC09, TC21, TC27-TC29, TC46-TC50).
Query Parameters coverage: combinations of accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, and audit (TC03-07, TC26, TC29, TC42).
Authorization handling: authentication failures return 401 (TC15, TC16).
Input validation and error scenarios: invalid offset/limit/audit, malformed booleans/integers, and method not allowed (TC10-13, TC38, TC39, TC40).
Security tests: SQL injection and XSS attempts (TC23, TC24).
Reliability and recovery: service unavailability, timeouts and recovery steps (TC17, TC18, TC36, TC37).
Performance and concurrency: large data loads and concurrent requests (TC19, TC20).
Integration tests: dependency unavailability and audit-log consistency (TC32, TC33).
Accessibility checks: response structure and error messaging accessibility (TC34, TC35).
State variation tests: partially populated database and degraded performance (TC30, TC31).
Regression coverage: boundary and compatibility regressions (TC21, TC22).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling behavior is not tested (no tests for 429 or similar).
Caching behavior: absence of tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional requests (304).
Granular authorization scenarios: no test for 403 Forbidden (insufficient permissions).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to validate throttling and appropriate error responses under high load.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and 304 responses when data is unchanged.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions scenarios for authenticated users.
Consider additional tests for extreme header/input sizes and failure modes to strengthen resilience.
